name: Stephens Pond on the NPT
description: A view of Stephens Pond taken at the lip of the pond downhill from a perfectly situated lean-to where overnighters can enjoy a campfire over beautiful water. The pond is located just south of Lake Durant in Adirondack Park on the Northville-Placid Trail, a serene, gentle 139-mile path stretching over solitary woods and lakes in the North Country of New York State.
